==English==

===Etymology===
{{defdate|circa 1540}} From {{der|en|fr|réalité||quality of being real}}, from {{der|en|frm|realité||property, possession}}, from {{der|en|ML.|reālitās}}, from {{der|en|LL.|reālis||real}}, equivalent to {{suffix|en|real|ity}}. Recorded since 1550 as a legal term in the sense of “fixed property” (compare {{m|en|real estate}}, {{doublet|en|realty|notext=1}}); the sense “real existence” is attested from 1647.

